---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Quick Start" description="Get FruitFly up and running in minutes with Docker.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Quick Start</h1>
  <p class="text-muted mb-8">Get FruitFly running in minutes using Docker.</p>

  <!-- Prerequisites -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Prerequisites</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <svg class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
        </svg>
        <span><a href="https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">Docker</a> installed on your system</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <svg class="size-4 text-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
        </svg>
        <span>A PostgreSQL database (local or hosted)</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 1: Pull the image -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">1. Pull the Docker Image</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      Pull the latest FruitFly image from Docker Hub:
    </p>
    <div class="rounded-sm border border-base-300 bg-base-200/90 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-base-300/50 flex items-center justify-between">
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-muted">Terminal</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <span class="text-primary">$</span>
        <span class="text-base-content ml-2">docker pull goodway/fruitfly:latest</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 2: Start PostgreSQL -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">2. Start PostgreSQL</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      If you don't have a PostgreSQL database, start one with Docker:
    </p>
    <div class="rounded-sm border border-base-300 bg-base-200/90 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-base-300/50">
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-muted">Terminal</span>
      </div>
      <pre class="p-4 font-mono text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="text-muted" set:html={`docker run -d \\
  --name fruitfly-db \\
  -e POSTGRES_USER=postgres \\
  -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres \\
  -e POSTGRES_DB=fruitfly \\
  -v fruitfly_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data \\
  -p 5432:5432 \\
  postgres:16-alpine`} /></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 3: Run FruitFly -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">3. Run FruitFly</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      Start the FruitFly container:
    </p>
    <div class="rounded-sm border border-base-300 bg-base-200/90 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-base-300/50">
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-muted">Terminal</span>
      </div>
      <pre class="p-4 font-mono text-xs overflow-x-auto"><code class="text-muted" set:html={`docker run -d \\
  --name fruitfly \\
  -e DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres:postgres@host.docker.internal:5432/fruitfly \\
  -e SECRET_KEY_BASE=$(openssl rand -base64 48) \\
  -e PHX_HOST=localhost \\
  -p 4000:4000 \\
  goodway/fruitfly:latest`} /></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 p-4 rounded-sm border border-warning/30 bg-warning/5">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <svg class="size-4 text-warning mt-0.5 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
        </svg>
        <div class="text-sm">
          <p class="text-warning font-medium">Note</p>
          <p class="text-muted mt-1">
            On Linux, replace <code class="text-warning">host.docker.internal</code> with your host's IP address or use <code class="text-warning">--network host</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 4: Access the app -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">4. Access FruitFly</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      Open your browser and navigate to:
    </p>
    <div class="rounded-sm border border-base-300 bg-base-200/90 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <a href="http://localhost:4000" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary hover:underline">
          http://localhost:4000
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mt-4">
      Create an account, then navigate to the dashboard to create your first project and start tracking issues.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 5: Create an API Key -->
  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">5. Create an API Key</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
      To use the API or CLI, you'll need an API key:
    </p>
    <ol class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted list-decimal list-inside">
      <li>Log in to your FruitFly dashboard</li>
      <li>Navigate to <strong class="text-base-content">Settings → API Keys</strong></li>
      <li>Click <strong class="text-base-content">Create API Key</strong></li>
      <li>Choose the key type:
        <ul class="ml-6 mt-1 space-y-1">
          <li><code class="text-primary">pk_*</code> — Read-only access</li>
          <li><code class="text-primary">sk_*</code> — Full read/write access</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Copy and securely store your API key</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <!-- Next steps -->
  <section class="pt-6 border-t border-base-300/30">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Next Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <a href="/docs/authentication/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors">
        <svg class="size-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        Learn about API authentication
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/api/issues/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors">
        <svg class="size-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        Create your first issue via API
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/cli/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors">
        <svg class="size-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
        Set up the CLI tool
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
